# Use Bun

This project uses **Bun** (not npm or yarn) for:

- **Install dependencies:** `bun install` (never `npm install`)
- **Add packages:** `bun add <pkg>` (never `npm install <pkg>`)
- **Run scripts:** `bun run <script>` or `bun <script>` when supported (e.g. `bun dev`)
- **Dev server:** `bun dev`
- **Build/start:** `bun run build`, `bun run start`

When suggesting or running terminal commands, always use `bun` instead of `npm` or `yarn`.
